Package curam.util.type

Contains the fundamental object type classes that are used by the Curam.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DateRanged
    Indicates that the object contains a date range, typically signifying the "lifetime" of the object by virtue of a start and/or end date.
    DateTimeRanged
    Indicates that the object contains a date/time range, typically signifying the "lifetime" of the object by virtue of a start and/or end date/time.
    DeepCloneable
    DeepCloneable is an interface which must be implemented by all Curam value objects to indicate that are responsible for cloning themselves.
    HistoricalEvent
    Signifies that the entity stores a history of events (typically state changes).

    Blob represents a chunk of binary data.
    CodeTable
    Retrieve code table translations.
    CodeTableEntry
    An entry from a Curam code table.
    CodetableHelper

    CodeTableItemIdentifier
    This class uniquely identifies a code table item.
    Date
    `Curam's` fundamental Date data-type.
    DateRange
    Holds a period of time bounded by a start date and end date.
    DateRange.DateRangeSet<D extends DateRanged>
    A date range and the entities covered by that date range.
    DateTime
    Represents a Curam DateTime as a Java millisecond value.
    DateTimeRange
    Holds a period of time bounded by a start date/time and end date/time.
    FrequencyPattern

Package curam.util.type Description

Contains the fundamental object type classes that are used by the Curam. The main classes include Date, which is the Curam date Object, DateTime, the Curam date and time Object, and Frequency Pattern, which is a flexible way of defining frequencies within Curam.

For more information consult the Curam Developer's guide.

Since:
Curam SDEJ3.0.0
